## Vault Structure

This vault uses the **three-layer model**:

| Layer | Purpose | Folders |
|---|---|---|
| **1. Canon** | The universe: entities, lore, source material | `world/`{% if include_sources %}, `sources/`{% endif %} |
| **2. Creative** | What you build on canon: plot, systems | `story/`{% if project_type != 'generic' %}, `mechanics/`{% endif %} |
{% if project_type == 'ttrpg' %}| **3. Production** | What you bring to the table | `play/` |
{% endif %}
### Folders

- `world/` — all entities (characters, locations, items, factions, lore). Flat, no subfolders. Navigate via Bases views and wikilinks.
{% if include_sources %}- `sources/` — raw or cleaned source material with attribution
{% endif %}- `story/` — scenes, plot arcs, narrative structure
{% if project_type != 'generic' %}- `mechanics/` — game systems, rules, stat blocks
{% endif %}{% if project_type == 'ttrpg' %}- `play/` — session prep, session logs, encounters
{% endif %}- `templates/` — note templates (use Obsidian's Insert Template)
- `views/` — Bases view definitions
- `assets/` — images, audio, media

## Properties

All notes use frontmatter properties:

| Property | Values | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `type` | `character`, `location`, `item`, `faction`, `lore`, `scene`{% if project_type == 'ttrpg' %}, `session-prep`, `session-log`, `encounter`{% endif %} | Note type identifier |
| `status` | `draft`, `ready`, `revealed`, `retired` | Content lifecycle |
| `canon` | `true` / `false` | Is this canonical to the universe? |
| `source` | string | Attribution (e.g., `"self"`, `"Author 2024"`) |
| `genai` | `true` / `false` | AI-generated content flag |

## Conventions

- **Naming:** lowercase kebab-case for all files and folders
- **Templates:** one per note type in `templates/`, flat
- **Views:** Bases `.base` files in `views/`
- **Dashboard:** `home.md` is the vault entry point
- **New notes:** always use a template; place entities in `world/`, scenes in `story/`{% if project_type == 'ttrpg' %}, session notes in `play/`{% endif %}
- **Wikilinks:** link entities to each other using `[[entity-name]]`; use in frontmatter for structured relationships

## Canon Rules

- Default `canon: true`. Everything established IS canon unless marked otherwise.
- Mark `canon: false` for non-canonical additions (filler NPCs, what-if scenarios).
- Always set `source` to a meaningful attribution string. Use `"self"` for original content.
- Set `genai: false` for human-written content, `true` for AI-generated.
{% if include_sources %}
## Source Ingestion

To ingest source material into this vault, use the `/ingest-source` command. The workflow:

1. Source material (chapter, wiki page, reference) goes into `sources/` as a source note
2. Entities are extracted and created/updated in `world/` using templates
3. Existing entities are updated additively (never overwrite user edits)
4. Wikilinks are created between related entities

When creating entities from source material, set `canon: true` and `source` to the attribution string. Set `genai: false` (the source is human-written, even if an agent does the extraction).
{% endif %}
## Agent Scaffold

This vault includes an agent scaffold in `.claude/`:

- **`.claude/skills/`** — Obsidian knowledge (kepano base) + Grimoire conventions (grimoire-overlay) + project-specific canon ({{ project_name }}-canon)
- **`.claude/commands/`** — Worldbuilding workflow commands

Read the grimoire-overlay skill for detailed property schema and conventions.

## Working With This Vault

- Start from `home.md` for an overview
- Use existing templates when creating notes
- Keep `world/` flat (no subfolders), use properties and links for organization
- Use Bases views in `views/` to browse and filter entities
- Set `canon: false` for non-canonical content
- Set `genai: true` on any AI-generated content
